<HEADLINE>
FT  17 OCT 94 / Business Travel (Update): Danish road/rail link
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Denmark's Prince Joachim became the first person to walk under the Great
Belt strait at the weekend, through a railway tunnel that is Denmark's
largest engineering project. The five-mile tunnel is part of a rail and road
link across the strait that separates Copenhagen on the main Baltic island
of Zealand, from the Jutland peninsula.
The last part of the DKr21.6bn (Pounds 2.27bn) project, a road bridge which
will connect Zealand to the island of Sprogo, is under construction. Trains
are expected to cross the Great Belt in 1996, and road traffic the year
after.
