FT  17 OCT 94 / Wimbledon tennis to stay with BBC
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The BBC said yesterday it had won the right to televise the Wimbledon tennis
championships for the next five years. Its contract with the All England
Lawn Tennis Club means the championships will be shown on the BBC until
1999.
The new contract will allow the club to offer highlights and delayed rights
to satellite and cable broadcasters.
