FT  17 OCT 94 / Demand rises for factory floorspace
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Available factory and warehouse floorspace in England and Wales has dropped
3 per cent in the past four months - the first substantial fall for five
years, King Sturge, the chartered surveyors, said.
Its survey shows reductions falls in most regions, suggesting a marked rise
in demand. The biggest drop was in north-west England.
