<HEADLINE>
FT  17 OCT 94 / Lamont resigns from Bow Group
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Mr Norman Lamont, the former chancellor who sparked a row at the Tory
conference, has quit the Bow Group after 30 years' membership.
He is believed to have quit the Tory think-tank because he was angry about
its refusal to stage his speech at the party conference fringe last week in
which he suggested Britain could leave the European Union. He eventually
made the speech at a fringe meeting organised by the rightwing Selsdon
Group.
The Bow Group said: 'We didn't want to give him a platform because we gave
him one at last year's conference and he delivered his alternative budget.
We're a broad-church organisation . . . and we didn't want to be seen to be
giving Norman Lamont a platform every time he asked for it.'
