<TEXT>
The Royal Navy's last diesel-powered submarine, HMS Unicorn, sailed into
mothballs yesterday - just 15 months after being accepted into service. The
move is a result of the end of the Cold War.
When Unicorn was designed the Cold War was still on and the role of the
Upholder Class was to release nuclear submarines for tackling other Nato
roles.
