FT  17 OCT 94 / Staff canteen 'perk' worth Pounds 300 a year
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The staff canteen is a 'substantial perk' worth at least Pounds 300 a year
to workers, a report says today.
The survey of 800 businesses by the Industrial Society and Touche Ross
Management Consultants says more workers than ever use office restaurants
because of the harsh realities of the economic climate.
Most of those surveyed contracted out catering services, with companies
paying an average subsidy of Pounds 328.90 a year per worker. Some paid up
to Pounds 600.
More than half the 500,000 workers covered by the survey said that they used
the staff canteen.
The Industrial Society said: 'We are seeing a new, competitive era for staff
restaurants and employees are realising what good value they really are.'
