<HEADLINE>
FT  15 OCT 94 / World Commodities Prices: Spices
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
After five or six weeks of hectic trading and rapidly rising prices the
black pepper market has entered a quiteter period, reports Man Producten.
Prices started to decline and buyers withdrew from the market, but we
consider quite a normal development and there are indications that prices
are stabilising already. Offers from origins remained limited to a small
number of profit-takers only. Black faq spot Europe traded yesterday at
USDollars 2,550 a tonne and in the US Market the ASTA grade was at 1.30
cents a pound, 5 cents lower than last week. White pepper prices were only
marginally lower but the activity was equally reduced. Muntok white spot
Europe ended Dollars 3,400 a tonne.
</TEXT>
